      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Key examples of substantive due process in action involve landmark decisions related to individual autonomy and privacy. For instance, cases like *Griswold v. Connecticut* struck down laws restricting access to contraception, establishing a fundamental right to marital privacy. Furthermore, precedents related to bodily integrity and liberty have been used to limit governmental power in areas of personal decision-making. These cases demonstrate how the doctrine serves as a shield, allowing courts to invalidate legislation that infringes on deeply held, fundamental rights.",
      "source": "target",
